The class test is a port scanning program. It takes in a range of IPs and ports to scan and attempts to make a connection to each of them. While doing so it produces a text file report on the results of the scan

inMySubnet

public static Boolean inMySubnet(String outsideIp,
                                 FileOutputStream out)
isMySubnet checks if a given IP address is a part of the users subnet. This is done by obtaining the subnet and IP of the user and then comparing the relavent bits of the two IPs. Relavent bits are determind by the subnet mask

Parameters:
String - The IP to be checked to see if it's part of the subnet
FileOutputStream - The output stream to the file that's being written to

portIsOpen

public static Future<Boolean> portIsOpen(ExecutorService es,
                                         String ip,
                                         int port,
                                         int timeout,
                                         FileOutputStream out)
portIsOpen checks if a given port is open by attempting to make a socket and connect to a secified IP and port number with a given timeout value. It uses a future callble so that this test can be done symultaneously with other test. The function asking for the result of this test will wait until that result is available.

Parameters:
ExecutorService - The systems executor service
String - The IP address that should be scanned
int - port The port to be scanned
int - timeout The time that a connection should be waited for
FileOutputStream - The output stream to the report file that is being written
Returns:
Future Whether or not the port is open
